      "hypothesis": "vel 20-50 + dd>-10% is the most regime-stable combo in the catalog (n=111, opt +5.13% @ tp=150/sl=30, STABLE wr_std_dev=2.8%). Live v10-best-double underperforms research at median -4.34% on n=37, attributed to entry gate mismatch (-99..1000 vs research +5..+100) and possibly SL (25 vs grid-optimal 30). v20-base deploys corrected gate to A/B-test the gate hypothesis directly against v10 (kept untouched as control). v20-tight tightens dd from -10% to -7%. v20-sl20 stress-tests the SL grid optimum — at n=92 the optimum was sl=25, at n=111 it shifted to sl=30; if v20-sl20 outperforms v20-base, the grid optimum is noisy. At n=50 per variant, the gate hypothesis confirms if v20-base median > v10 median by 5pp+.",
